import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['job'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Job')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of job types in the dataset?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('sex').sum()
    plt.pie(data['count'], labels=data.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('How does the count of males and females compare in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of count over the years in the dataset?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    job_perc = data[['job', 'perc']].groupby(['job']).sum()
    job_perc.plot(kind='pie', y='perc', legend=False, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.title('What is the percentage distribution of job types in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['job', 'sex']).sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['job'], data[data['sex'] == 'M']['count'], label='Male')
    ax.bar(data['job'], data[data['sex'] == 'F']['count'], bottom=data[data['sex'] == 'M']['count'], label='Female')
    ax.set_xlabel('Job')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('How does the count of males and females vary across job types in the dataset?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
